# Resource Generation Rules

## Naming Convention
- Use PascalCase for resource keys
- Follow the pattern: `{TargetName}{ElementType}.{Property}`
  - Example: `FiltersTextBox.Header`
  - Example: `FiltersTextBox.PlaceholderText`

## Structure
- Use consistent naming across all pages

## Content Guidelines
- Keep text concise and clear
- Use consistent terminology

## File Organization
- Maintain separate files for each language
- Keep resource files in sync across languages
- Use proper XML formatting and spacing